"{'title': \"Highly diverse and unknown viruses may enhance Antarctic endoliths' adaptability\", 'authors': [{'forename': 'Cassandra', 'surname': 'Ettinger', 'email': 'cassande@ucr.edu', 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Microbiology and Plant Pathology', 'affiliation_country': 'USA'}, {'forename': 'Morgan', 'surname': 'Saunders', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Biological Sciences', 'affiliation_country': 'USA'}, {'forename': 'Laura', 'surname': 'Selbmann', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Ecological and Biological Sciences', 'affiliation_country': 'Italy'}, {'forename': 'Manuel', 'surname': 'Delgado-Baquerizo', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Laboratorio de Biodiversidad Y Funcionamiento Ecosist\u00e9mico', 'affiliation_country': 'Spain'}, {'forename': 'Claudio', 'surname': 'Donati', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Research and Innovation Centre', 'affiliation_country': 'Italy'}, {'forename': 'Davide', 'surname': 'Albanese', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Research and Innovation Centre', 'affiliation_country': 'Italy'}, {'forename': 'Simon', 'surname': 'Roux', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Energy Joint Genome Institute', 'affiliation_country': 'USA'}, {'forename': 'Susannah', 'surname': 'Tringe', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Energy Joint Genome Institute', 'affiliation_country': 'USA'}, {'forename': 'Christa', 'surname': 'Pennacchio', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Energy Joint Genome Institute', 'affiliation_country': 'USA'}, {'forename': 'Tijana', 'surname': 'Del Rio', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Energy Joint Genome Institute', 'affiliation_country': 'USA'}, {'forename': 'Jason', 'surname': 'Stajich', 'email': None, 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Microbiology and Plant Pathology', 'affiliation_country': 'USA'}, {'forename': 'Claudia', 'surname': 'Coleine', 'email': 'coleine@unitus.it', 'affiliation_name': 'Department of Microbiology and Plant Pathology', 'affiliation_country': 'USA'}], 'abstract': 'Background Rock-dwelling microorganisms are key players in ecosystem functioning of Antarctic ice free-areas. Yet, little is known about their diversity and ecology, and further still, viruses in these communities have been largely unexplored despite important roles related to host metabolism and nutrient cycling. To begin to address this, we present a large-scale viral catalog from Antarctic rock microbial communities.\\nResultsWe performed metagenomic analyses on rocks from across Antarctica representing a broad range of environmental and spatial conditions, and which resulted in a predicted viral catalog comprising > 75,000 viral operational taxonomic units (vOTUS). We found largely undescribed, highly diverse and spatially structured virus communities which had predicted auxiliary metabolic genes (AMGs) with functions indicating that they may be potentially influencing bacterial adaptation and biogeochemistry.\\nConclusionThis catalog lays the foundation for expanding knowledge of virosphere diversity, function, spatial ecology, and dynamics in extreme environments. This work serves as a step towards exploring adaptability of microbial communities in the face of a changing climate.', 'acknowledgements': '<ontology_classes.Aknowledgement object at 0x00000293751FB010>', 'references': [{'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x000002937520DF90>, 'date': '2016'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x000002937520E590>, 'date': '2018'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x000002937520E890>, 'date': '2019'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x000002937520E910>, 'date': '2020'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x000002937520E990>, 'date': '2021'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x000002937520EA50>, 'date': '2022'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x000002937520EAD0>, 'date': '2010'}, {'cites': <ontology_classes.Paper object at 0x0